newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see nearby soymeal trade in afternoon.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see nearby soymeal trade in afternoon.

text.p: The European meals and feeds market saw nearby soymeal trade this afternoon at firmer prices as prompt material is scarce in Europe, market sources said.

"It is difficult getting prompt soymeal as little unsold material arrives into Europe, while crushers here still not run at full capacity due to the late arrival of beans from North America, therefore prices for nearby material soar," one broker said.
Neaarby afloat Argentine soymeal pellets traded $9 up from yesterday at $291 a tonne cif. Dec shipment traded at $281 a tonne cif Rotterdam, which is $24 up from Nov 4.
